<a name="3193"></a>

<div class="sub-content-header">Big Announcements at CES – Keynotes and Exhibitor Registration!</div>
<br />

<IMG hspace=10 vspace=5 align=right src="/images/photos/ballmer-1-1.jpg" width=100 height=140>Two big announcements were recently made here at CES HQ. First, last week it was announced that Microsoft’s Steve Ballmer and Intel’s Paul Otellini will once again <A href="/sessions/keynotes.asp" target=_blank>keynote at the 2010 CES</A>. <BR><BR>“This year’s CES is more important for the technology industry than ever. These two business leaders will provide actionable direction on what it takes to succeed in the global marketplace,” said Gary Shapiro, president and CEO, CEA.&nbsp; “CES is the must-attend event where business gets done and where the Microsoft and Intel chiefs will share with CES attendees a strategic vision for business success.”<BR><BR><IMG hspace=10 vspace=5 align=left src="/images/photos/Intel_Otellini_10.jpg" width=100 height=134>Steve Ballmer, chief executive officer of Microsoft, will kick off the 2010 International CES keynote lineup at 6:30 p.m. on Wednesday, January 6, in the Hilton Center. Paul Otellini, president and chief executive officer of Intel Corporation, will speak at 4:30 p.m. on Thursday, January 7, in the Hilton Center.<BR><BR>It was also announced last week that <A href="/exhibitors/exhibitorBadges.asp" target=_blank>exhibitor registration</A> is now open. It is now time to <A href="/exhibitors/exhibitorBadges.asp" target=_blank>register</A> your booth staff and top 10 buyers. Register by <STRONG>December 7, 2009</STRONG>, to have your badges mailed to you. No request for badge mailing after this date will be guaranteed. Even though badges will be mailed until December 21, we cannot guarantee delivery of badges after December 7 due to holiday traffic.<BR><BR>Questions? Contact International CES Exhibitor Registration Customer Service at 866-233-7968 or <A href="mailto:exhreg@CE.org">exhreg@CE.org</A>.
        <br /><img width="1" height="20" src="/images/framework/spacer.gif"/>
        <img height="15" alt="" src="/images/framework/divider-line.gif"/><br />

<a name="3188"></a>

<div class="sub-content-header">CES Exhibitor Workshop – Now Online!</div>
<br />

<IMG height=172 hspace=10 src="/images/photos/computer1.jpg" width=200 align=right vspace=10>New this year, the <A href="/exhibitors/resources/workshop.asp">2010 International CES Exhibitor Workshop</A> will be offered as an online series. This free, four-part webcast series starts in&nbsp;September and shows you how to use CES to market and promote your brand and receive the ultimate press coverage. Plus, it will turn you into a pro when dealing with booth planning and logistics. You’ll also hear expert advice from exhibitors who have helpful tips to pass along.&nbsp;<BR><BR><A href="/exhibitors/resources/workshop.asp">Registering for any workshop webcast</A> also gives you access to the 2010 Exhibitor Workshop online community where you can: 
<UL class=text>
<LI class=text>Participate in discussion board chats with other exhibitors. </LI>
<LI class=text>Access CES official vendor discount codes to receive discounts available from the likes of GES, Smart City and Encore. </LI>
<LI class=text>Download important deadline dates and calendar. </LI>
<LI class=text>View archived webcasts.</LI></UL><A href="/exhibitors/resources/workshop.asp">See times, dates and descriptions for all webcasts, and register today!</A>
        <br /><img width="1" height="20" src="/images/framework/spacer.gif"/>
        <img height="15" alt="" src="/images/framework/divider-line.gif"/><br />

<a name="3187"></a>

<div class="sub-content-header">Send Us Your PR Contact Information</div>
<br />

<IMG height=134 hspace=10 src="/images/photos/PR1.jpg" width=200 align=right vspace=10>Leverage the CES PR tools and resources before, during and after the 2010 International CES by sending us your PR contact information. <BR><BR>To ensure that the media can find you at CES, please take a moment to list your company’s PR contact. We will direct any media inquiries we receive regarding your company or products to the individual you indicate. The contact information will be available to all registered CES media.&nbsp;It is required that you go to your <A href="https://myces.bdmetrics.com/exhibitorportal/EventLogin.aspx" target=_blank>MyCES Exhibitor Portal</A> to add/update your PR contact information. <BR><BR>Questions? Contact Allison Fried at <A href="mailto:afried@CE.org">afried@CE.org</A>.
        <br /><img width="1" height="20" src="/images/framework/spacer.gif"/>
        <img height="15" alt="" src="/images/framework/divider-line.gif"/><br />

<a name="3186"></a>

<div class="sub-content-header">Innovations 2010 Wants Your Brilliant Designs!</div>
<br />

<IMG height=150 hspace=10 src="/images/content/CES_251_2k10_Innovations.jpg" width=98 align=right vspace=10>The <A href="/awards/innovations/default.asp" target=_blank>International CES<SUP>&reg;</SUP> Innovations 2010 Design and Engineering Awards</A> is the most impressive and renowned awards program in the consumer technology industry. Thousands of industry leaders and press flock to CES to witness the “next big thing” at the Innovations 2010 Design and Engineering Awards Showcase. <BR><BR>Receive all the recognition your brilliant new designs and products deserve by entering the competition at <A href="/awards/innovations/default.asp" target=_blank>CESweb.org/Innovations</A>. The Call for Entries is open August 24-September 25, but enter by September 4 to save $200 on the entry fee. <BR><BR>Being an Innovations Honoree provides you with incredible opportunities, special recognition in the CE industry and worldwide exposure for your company and products. Visit CESweb.org/Innovations for complete details, benefits and to enter your product on August 24!
        <br /><img width="1" height="20" src="/images/framework/spacer.gif"/>
        <img height="15" alt="" src="/images/framework/divider-line.gif"/><br />

<a name="3185"></a>

<div class="sub-content-header">Expand your Global Reach</div>
<br />

<IMG hspace=10 vspace=10 align=right src="/images/photos/Globe1.jpg" width=200 height=200>Interested in exporting? Plan to participate in our Exporting Exhibitor Program. The program is complimentary for all CES exhibitors. Benefits include: 
<UL class=text>
<LI class=text>Post-show list pull with contact information for attendees from up to 10 countries you select. </LI>
<LI class=text>Complimentary tickets to the international reception. </LI>
<LI class=text>Export counseling services provided by the U.S. Department of Commerce. </LI></UL>To participate in this program, you must indicate that you are interested in exporting opportunities when you complete your online listing in the <A href="https://myces.bdmetrics.com/exhibitorportal/EventLogin.aspx" target=_blank>MyCES Exhibitor Portal</A>. <BR><BR>If more than 51 percent of your product is manufactured in the U.S., you also qualify to participate in the Global Market Insight Program, organized by the U.S. Department of Commerce’s Commercial Service, in cooperation with the Consumer Electronics Association (CEA)<SUP>&reg;</SUP>. As part of this program, the Commercial Service is offering meetings between U.S. exhibitors and consumer electronics industry specialists from U.S. embassies around the world who will be attending the 2010 International CES.&nbsp; <A href="/docs/CES_2010_GMIP_flyer._ICC_TBD.pdf" target=_blank>Learn more about this program</A>.
        <br /><img width="1" height="20" src="/images/framework/spacer.gif"/>
        <img height="15" alt="" src="/images/framework/divider-line.gif"/><br />

<a name="3184"></a>

<div class="sub-content-header">The 2009 SINOCES a Huge Success</div>
<br />

<IMG height=60 hspace=10 src="/images/content/SINOCES_LOGO_180.jpg" width=180 align=right vspace=10>The sixth annual SINOCES, China’s largest exhibition of consumer technology, was held July 9-12, 2009, in Qingdao, China. Industry professionals from around the globe experienced the latest products across the largest show floor in SINOCES history. <BR><BR>“The Chinese consumer electronics market is one of the strongest in the world and is expected to reach $100 billion by the end of 2009. SINOCES provides unprecedented exposure for technology companies looking to break into this booming market,” said Gary Shapiro, president and CEO, CEA. “CEA’s partnership with the China Electronics Chamber of Commerce and the City of Qingdao has enabled SINOCES to grow into China’s largest technology trade event.” <BR><BR>Please contact a CES representative to learn how your company can participate in China’s premier consumer electronics show for industry professionals. For more information on the 2009 SINOCES, visit <A href="http://www.SINOCES.com" target=_blank>www.SINOCES.com</A>. 
